        "D. The known or potential error rate of the methodology"
      ],
      "correct": 2,
      "justification_correct": "The Daubert Standard focuses on objective and verifiable indicators of methodological reliability—not on the expert's subjective belief or personal confidence in their own results. (Daubert v. Merrell Dow)",
